<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-09-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-09-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7636: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-14T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 14,
                                        1926—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>192. Your 400, September 14, 5 p.m. Instructions to consul at Swatow
                            referred to in paragraph 2 are approved. See in this connection your 447
                            of October 16, 7 p.m., 1925, and Department’s 308 of October 29, 6
                                p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d478fn27"><ref target="frus1925v01#pg_746"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1925, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 746</ref> and <ref target="frus1925v01#pg_747">747</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>